Claude Code Expert should not just explain Claude Code. It should deploy an advanced agentic coding operating system.

That operating system should help a user:

structure memory

choose the right execution runtime

launch specialized workers

react to external events

run unattended on schedules

recover from context loss

verify work before completion

scale from one repo to recurring engineering operations

Single strongest build prompt
Use the claude-code-expert plugin directory as the implementation target. Build the next major version around a real autonomy operating system, not just reference content. Add a /cc-autonomy command, workflow packs, a channels bootstrap system, a scheduled-task generator, headless automation support, a hooks policy engine, memory deployment, subagent role packs, agent-team topology kits, and advisory MCP tools that recommend the right execution pattern for each engineering task.

